The Special Adviser to Oyo State Governor Seyi Makinde on Labour Matters, Comrade Bayo Titilola-Sodo, has said that the second term of the governor will be better than the first term. He made this disclosure when he hosted members of Nigeria Union of Journalists (NUJ) Oyo state council at a Iftar (fast breaking) in his residence in Ibadan. The special adviser who said that the governor has performed well, insisted that the second term will be better than the first one. Titilola-Sodo who acknowledged that no government can satisfy everyone, added that journalists have a role to criticise those in positions of authority constructively. He described the NUJ as a versatile union that has been helping to shape the current democracy. According to him, “NUJ is a versatile union to associate with. I want to say thank you and appreciate what you have done. No government can satisfy everyone. It is your job to criticise constructively. “You have been constructive partners in the running the affairs of Oyo state. It is my hope that we will do better than the first term”.‒‒:‒‒/‒‒:‒‒